passwords have been around in computing since the 1960's, and using them as a means of protecting sensitive information is badly outdated. they can be guessed, brute-forced, and stolen. hackers have used compromised passwords to perpetrate almost every major computer system break-in in recent years. it's time to do something about it. bloksec's patent-pending approach to account security uses a decentralized authentication system built on blockchain technology. when a user authenticates, the record is immutable, verifiable, secure, and cannot be repudiated. there are no passwords or personally identifiable information stored on bloksec servers so there is no central repository to be attacked. and accessing your secure account is as easy as unlocking your phone.

iut, is a desulphurization technology provider that own 8 us patents and 1 provisional patent (filed under pct/worldwide). there are 2 generations of the technology. the first generation technology/unit is fully developed and was previously commercially validated in a texas refinery. the first generation technology removes sulphur from lighter fossil fuel oils like condensate, naptha, diesel, natural gasoline, etc. the unit has a processing capability of 6,000 bpd. the second generation version of our technology is focused on the desulphurization of heavy fuel oils (ex. marine gas oil, bunker fuel, etc.) (approx. 4,000 bpd unit capacity) and is in the final stages of r&d with 6 - 8 months left before moving to commercialization. we have processed hfo feedstock samples and have proof of concept - i.e.were able to reduce the sulphur content of the hfo feedstocks down to an average of 0.5% or less, which coincides with the minimum requirements of the imo 2020 regulations.

semanti.ca is an ai-powered scalable web article data extraction api. to extract data, semanti.ca loads a web article in a browser and reads it, just like humans do. semanti.ca accurately recognizes titles, headlines, published and updated dates, images, captions, tags. it extracts the content text and the html code, by ignoring advertisements, the design elements, and any other text or image not related to the main content. semanti.ca is not tailored to some specific website user interface designs or technology. it is trained on hundreds of thousands of examples and is capable of recognizing relevant elements on the web page, independently of how the web page was built. it actually "looks" at the web pages and recognizes the content based on a statistical model learned from data. furthermore, semanti.ca classifies the extracted content based on the iptc media topics taxonomy and extracts key phrases from the text. this helps our users to organize the extracted content.

the problem we are solving is the counterfeiting of western products in china. chinese consumers distrust domestic manufacturing due to countless product safety and counterfeiting scandals. there is a $15b industry (daigou) where chinese consumers pay overseas shoppers to ship them goods from countries like canada. the same products are usually available in china, but consumers believe the product is safer if it was purchased elsewhere. puremark lets anyone verify the authenticity of a product, giving the chinese buyer peace-of-mind when buying domestically, while protecting market share and maximizing authentic sales volumes. our beachhead industry is canadian icewine (50% of the icewine in china is fake). we embed unclonable nfc chips into wine bottles, allowing the chinese buyer (e.g. a shopper in a store) to download our app and tap the bottle with their phone to verify its authenticity. the chip breaks when the bottle is opened, so a counterfeiter cannot refill used bottles.

magnetic resonance images (mris) aren't utilized to their full potential because they are subjectively evaluated, often leaving out crucial quantitative information. this quantitative information is slow and expensive to obtain because first, the mri needs to be segmented. segmentation can be thought of as colouring in an mri to identify the structures of interest (i.e. tumour, cartilage). segmentation is slow because an mri is made up of hundreds of individual images and manually colouring each image takes hours. segmentations provide quantitative metrics and help plan for surgeries by viewing 3d models, or 3d printing structures. current algorithms are slow, with reported segmentation times of 30 minutes to 2 days. neuralseg uses deep learning, and segments with an accuracy equivalent to the best reported. neuralseg's primary advantage is that it segments mris in 2-minutes. we are harnessing this efficiency to offer on-demand image segmentation via a web-application.

every year crop farmers run the risk of acquiring the highly contagious, soil-borne disease clubroot, which has the potential to devastate up to 80% of their annual yields. once infected with this disease, it takes farmers up to twenty years to rid the soil of it completely. in alberta alone, there have been 2000 farms that have been infected with clubroot. cropcure is the first natural-based soil treatment that targets clubroot specifically. unlike competitors, cropcure is non-toxic. our powdered formula works with farmers existing machinery (double-barreled seeder) during the seeding process. once the clubroot starts to form, the farmer will realize the need to take action and prompt the use of cropcure. the powder penetrates the topsoil, increasing its alkalinity and making the ground inhospitable to clubroot. the disease causing spores are then essentially frozen in place and unable to reproduce. in as little as 6 weeks, cropcure can reduce the severity and duration of clubroot.
